## How to Use This File

- **Reviewer**: Score outputs against these criteria. Flag when a criterion is met or violated.
- **Analyst**: Use these criteria to structure your findings. Propose new criteria or retire weak ones.
- **Orchestrator**: After each cycle, check whether the rubric needs updating based on what was learned. Add open questions. Remove resolved ones.

---

## Scoring Rules

- The **regression test set** is for **breakage detection** — not quality benchmarking. Scores on regression cases are informational but may be inflated by overfitting.
- Use the full 1-10 range with decimals for precision.
- 1-2: Broken, unusable. 3-4: Poor, significant issues. 5-6: Acceptable, works but weak. 7-8: Good, minor issues. 9: Very good. 10: Exceptional.
- **Score honestly.** If quality is 6.5, say 6.5 — don't round up to make progress look better.

